properties.Name: Branch
properties.Description:
A Bank site or location that sells Bank Products.

A branch is any banking facility away from a bank's main office that accepts deposits or makes loans.

State laws strictly control branches of state and national banks.     Savings and loan and thrift institutions have been generally exempted.   

A Branch may be a full-service branch or a mini-branch.
A mini-branch is a specialized branch office that offers a limited number of banking services.
